defs.docs: Provides abstractions for working with bytes.

defs.name: buf
defs.docs: Utilities for working with buffers.

defs.name: Buf
defs.docs: Read bytes from a buffer.

defs.name: remaining
defs.docs:
Returns the number of bytes between the current position and the end of
 the buffer.

defs.name: bytes
defs.docs:
Returns a slice starting at the current position and of length between 0
 and `Buf::remaining()`. Note that this *can* return shorter slice (this allows
 non-continuous internal representation).

defs.name: bytes_vec
defs.docs:
Fills `dst` with potentially multiple slices starting at `self`'s
 current position.

defs.name: remaining_mut
defs.docs:
Returns the number of bytes that can be written from the current

defs.name: advance_mut
defs.docs: Advance the internal cursor of the BufMut

defs.name: has_remaining_mut
defs.docs: Returns true if there is space in `self` for more bytes.

defs.name: bytes_mut
defs.docs:
Returns a mutable slice starting at the current BufMut position and of
 length between 0 and `BufMut::remaining_mut()`. Note that this *can* be shorter than the
 whole remainder of the buffer (this allows non-continuous implementation).
